From Sylvanus Viashima, Jalingo Gunmen have abducted a state lawmaker representing Nguroje Constituency in the Taraba State House of Assembly, Alhaji Bashir Mohammed, in the early hours of Wednesday, December 9. A family source says Mohammed, who is the Chairman, House Committee on Information, was picked up from his residence at about 1 am. As at the time of this report, the kidnappers were yet to make contact with the family. 